s to terrorism, disease, and environmental degradation—and in doing so provide a comprehensive look at the complexities of building peace and stability in modern-day Africa. Not only does the book critically assess the state of progress in addressing security challenges, but it presents new strategies and tools for more effectively engaging Africans and the global community in their common search for solutions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aHuman securityzAfrica. 0aInternal securityzAfrica. 0aNational securityzAfrica. 4aInternational Relations 2019. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / African.2bisacsh  aAfrican Union.  aDrug trafficking.  aEnvironmental degradation.  aEthnic and religious conflict.  aEuropean Union.  aFailed and failing states.  aHuman security.  aInternational engagement.  aPandemic disease.  aPeacekeeping and stability.  aTerrorism and counter-terrorism.  aUnited States.  aviolence and conflict.1 aEmerson, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSolomon, Hussein, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSolomon, Hussein, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packagez978311128277040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612274240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526122742423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526122742/original  a978-3-11-128277-0  Manchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packageb2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles